   <mods:abstract>Report on Madison√Üs resolutions of April 18th. Feels that the United
            States will lose much by transferring negotiations to Madrid. More honorable to have
            foreign powers send ambassadors to us. Also negotiator in closer touch with government
            if need for quick decision. Does not see what would be improved by change and Spain,
            suspicious, will think this is only a bid for time, not a means of improving the
            circumstances of negotiation. Doubts that Spain would enter into negotiations with
            Jefferson under terms of resolutions as they give him no power to conclude a treaty, but
            only to confer. If Congress does not agree with him on this point, however, Jefferson
            well qualified for task.</mods:abstract>
